==English==

===Etymology===

# From the Japanese [[円]], "en".
# From the English yen-yen, "craving for opium", from the Chinese yIn-yáhn, "opium craving".

===Noun===

'''yen''' (''plural'': '''yen''')

# A unit of Japanese currency, equal to 100 sen. (see: [[円]])
# A strong desire, urge, or yearning.

===Verb===

'''yen''' (''intransitive verb'': '''yenned''', '''yens''', '''yenning''')

# To have a strong desire, urge, or yearning.

===Synonyms===

[[yearning]], [[hankering]]